parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to occupants being trapped or unable to use the seat belt, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle is inoperative
the seat belt buckle is stuck
the seat belt buckle is broken
the seat belt buckle jams
the seat belt release mechanism is chipped
pieces fall into the locking mechanism
the seat belt buckle is extremely difficult to use.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the rear seat belts can cause occupants to be unbuckled or unable to use the seat belt, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The rear seat belts occasionally fail to buckle
the rear seat belts stick
making them unusable
the rear seat belts are intermittent.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of fuel injectors can cause poor engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and increased emissions, which can lead to engine stalling, decreased power, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls or hesitates
the engine has a rough or misfiring idle
the engine has a lack of power or acceleration
the fuel economy is decreased
the check engine light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to slip or hesitate when shifting gears, leading to loss of power, reduced acceleration, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the transmission makes unusual noises
the transmission warning light is illuminated
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.
